article.headline: N. Colorado 84, Sacramento St. 54
article.story: GREELEY, Colo. -- Devon Beitzel tied a career high with 32 points to help Northern Colorado wrap up the Big Sky Conference title with an 84-54 win over Sacramento State on Wednesday night. It was the first conference crown for Northern Colorado (19-10, 13-3) in more than two decades, when the squad was a member of the Division II North Central Conference. Elliott Lloyd, Tate Unruh and Mike Proctor contributed nine points each for the surging Bears, who've won five in a row. Jackson Carbajal led the Hornets (7-21, 4-12) with 17 points, while Alpha N'Diaye grabbed 15 rebounds. As the conference champions, Northern Colorado will host the Big Sky semifinals and championship next week with a spot in the NCAA tournament on the line.
